<div id="review_3890351625" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3890351625" />
    <a title="Gina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57881981-gina"><img alt="Gina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598393448p2/57881981.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3890351625?book_show_action=true">Mar 23, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gina" href="/user/show/57881981-gina">Gina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/33118174-to-wager-her-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3890351625" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6164700350116583310">This was my least favorite out of the Belle Meade series. It’s truly a matter of preference. It wasn’t poorly written — Tamera’s writing style is consistently good! For me, the story was just a little bit on the boring side. At 50% in, the romance still hadn’t taken off. Also, once the romance between the two characters did start to kindle, it didn’t really make sense to me based on the reasons Alexandra was initially not interested in Sy. She went from no feelings to feelings pretty quickly. I </span>
  <span id="freeText6164700350116583310" style="display:none">This was my least favorite out of the Belle Meade series. It’s truly a matter of preference. It wasn’t poorly written — Tamera’s writing style is consistently good! For me, the story was just a little bit on the boring side. At 50% in, the romance still hadn’t taken off. Also, once the romance between the two characters did start to kindle, it didn’t really make sense to me based on the reasons Alexandra was initially not interested in Sy. She went from no feelings to feelings pretty quickly. I even felt that way for Sy. His feelings for her happened so quickly without a whole lot of interaction. It all seemed underdeveloped and under-communicated to me. <br />The other aspects of the story were sweet and tugged at your heart. This time period is sometimes a difficult part of American history to read about, but Tamera always does a beautiful job honestly presenting the information in a delicate, but accurate way... and with heart.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6164700350116583310" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


