        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1804338171" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17026695317191218628">Such a sweet conclusion to one of my favorite series. I always love Tamera’s novels and how she weaves a fictional story using real people, places, and historical events from our nation’s past. This story takes place five years after the Civil War ended. It really focuses on freed slaves being educated, railroads being built, and all the racial struggles that were still very prominent. I loved how one of my favorite songs “Give Me Jesus” was sung and referred to throughout the book. Using this s</span>
  <span id="freeText17026695317191218628" style="display:none">Such a sweet conclusion to one of my favorite series. I always love Tamera’s novels and how she weaves a fictional story using real people, places, and historical events from our nation’s past. This story takes place five years after the Civil War ended. It really focuses on freed slaves being educated, railroads being built, and all the racial struggles that were still very prominent. I loved how one of my favorite songs “Give Me Jesus” was sung and referred to throughout the book. Using this song within the context of the story made the song even more special for me. Although this book wasn’t my favorite of the series, it was still a wonderful read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17026695317191218628" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

