        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2548379285" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10915579894814836867">Loved the characters and the history behind this story, and I appreciate that not every thread tied up neatly by the end, because that&apos;s how life really is. This is a great example of a novel that is romantic without being very physical. There&apos;s something else I really loved about this novel which is true about everything I&apos;ve read by Tamera Alexander. The hero and heroine have their own interests and goals, apart from finding love. Not every thought they entertained was about their love interes</span>
  <span id="freeText10915579894814836867" style="display:none">Loved the characters and the history behind this story, and I appreciate that not every thread tied up neatly by the end, because that's how life really is. This is a great example of a novel that is romantic without being very physical. There's something else I really loved about this novel which is true about everything I've read by Tamera Alexander. The hero and heroine have their own interests and goals, apart from finding love. Not every thought they entertained was about their love interest counterpart. They have their own quests. I love that. </span>
