<div id="review_2652878142" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2652878142" />
    <a title="Joleen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5543196-joleen"><img alt="Joleen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590521753p2/5543196.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2652878142?book_show_action=true">Jan 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joleen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joleen" href="/user/show/5543196-joleen">Joleen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/33118174-to-wager-her-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5543196-joleen?shelf=accident">accident</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5543196-joleen?shelf=tn-reads">tn-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5543196-joleen?shelf=christian-romance">christian-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5543196-joleen?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5543196-joleen?shelf=teaching">teaching</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5543196-joleen?shelf=railroad">railroad</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5543196-joleen?shelf=national-novel-reading-month">national-novel-reading-month</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2652878142" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17809069722507313242"><i>To Wager Her Heart</i> by <b>Tamera Alexander</b><br/><i>Genre</i>: Christian Fiction/Romance<br/><i>Format</i>: Kindle/Audiobook<br/><i>Timeframe</i>: 1871<br/><i>Location</i>: Nashville, TN<br/><u>Main Characters</u>: <br/><i>Alexandra Jamison</i>: 25 year old teacher<br/><i>Sylas Rutledge</i>: Railroad owner from Colorado<br/><br/>Wonderful history of Fisk University, founded by the American Missionary Association after the Civil War for the education of freedmen in Nashville, TN, set around the story of railroad owner Sylas Rutledge and single teacher Alexandra Jamison.<br/><br/>The story was set one yea</span>
  <span id="freeText17809069722507313242" style="display:none"><i>To Wager Her Heart</i> by <b>Tamera Alexander</b><br /><i>Genre</i>: Christian Fiction/Romance<br /><i>Format</i>: Kindle/Audiobook<br /><i>Timeframe</i>: 1871<br /><i>Location</i>: Nashville, TN<br /><u>Main Characters</u>: <br /><i>Alexandra Jamison</i>: 25 year old teacher<br /><i>Sylas Rutledge</i>: Railroad owner from Colorado<br /><br />Wonderful history of Fisk University, founded by the American Missionary Association after the Civil War for the education of freedmen in Nashville, TN, set around the story of railroad owner Sylas Rutledge and single teacher Alexandra Jamison.<br /><br />The story was set one year after a fateful railroad crash in which Alexandra’s fiancé was killed in the train engineered by Sylas Rutledge’s father. Both grieved, but because an investigation of the crash concluded that the engineer was at fault for the crash that killed many, Alexandra was anything but warm toward Sylas.<br /><br />But because of the persistence of this Colorado railroad man needing Alexandra to tutor him in Southern etiquette in business meetings, they began seeing beyond the horrible history they both shared to their endearing characteristics and personalities instead.<br /><br />This story included fascinating true facts around the famous Belle Meade Plantation, the Jubilee singers from the Fisk University, a railroad crash at Dutchman’s Curve outside Nashville, TN, and real-life characters such as Ella Shephard, the first black teacher at Fisk University, and General William Giles Harding, owner of Belle Meade Plantation.<br /><br />I enjoyed the constant references to Christ and witnesses to the gospel by the staff and choir members of the Fisk University, and by hymn writer Philip Paul Bliss, who in fact, died in a train crash along with his wife, also written into the story. <br /><br />Lots of quotables. One I underlined was how the author compared Romans 8:36 and Hebrews 12:11 with one character’s words of wisdom: <i>“There will always be someone who has suffered more—or less—than you. To think the person who has suffered more, in your estimation, is somehow more worthy is just as prideful in nature as thinking that the person who has suffered less, in your estimation, is not quite as holy as you are.” He smiled. “God alone sees our lives from start to finish and ordains what your suffering and mine will be. For He alone sees what we each must endure to become more like His Son and to be made ready for eternity. For though we all are His, we are not all the same.”</i><br /><br />My one issue with this book was the way it ended. It was as if the author realized there were too many words written and had to throw in one quick chapter to wrap it all up. It wasn’t tidy in the least, just abrupt. A quick ending to an otherwise pretty good book.<br /><br /><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fisk_University" rel="nofollow noopener"> Link to Fisk University </a></span>
  <a data-text-id="17809069722507313242" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


